wickeln.   aThis work presents theory surrounding the promotion of literacy and reading from a practical perspective. It aims to help librarians plan and implement projects to promote literacy and reading for users of all ages, from young children to seniors. Discussed topics range from early childhood literacy support to special programs for adolescent readers and music-assisted methods for the very elderly.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aLeseförderung. 0aÖffentliche Bibliothek. 4aLeseförderung. 4aReading promotion. 4apublic libraries. 4aÖffentliche Bibliotheken. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aBrandt, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library a Information Sc, Lib Reference 2014z9783110370263oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831103962490 cprintz978311033688740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033701340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110337013423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110337013.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014